commit.message:
Allow address_book as field for list -F

This adds the special field "address_book" to the valid fields that can
be selected with the --format option.

Fix #331.

Specify version (ranges) for dependencies

Atomicwrites and vobject are more or less abandoned and did not have a
release in a long time.  They are pinned to exact versions in case some
change upstream results in an unexpected release.

For the other packages I took a guess what a good version constraint
could be.  They are not thoroughly tested and I did not study the
release notes to check which version we need.
Fix type annotation

Refactor helper method _add_labelled_property

This removes the dict syntax from the argument and turns the label into
an explicit function argument.

Check test suite with mypy

The test suite has a considerable number of calls to out code so it can
serve as some usage examples that should be type checked.
Add type annotation and mypy config
Add type annotations to _add_labelled_object
Add type annotations to _add_private_object
Add type annotations to _add_post_address
Add type annotations to some _add_* helper methods
Move some type declarations from comments to annotations
Fix some linter warnings
Run the tests in the nix build

Remove setup.py

This finalizes the switch from the deprecated setup.py to
pyproject.toml.  Setuptools is still used internally but not on the
command line.  Use pip to install khard or build the version.py file.

See also pep 517 and 518 or
https://blog.ganssle.io/articles/2021/10/setup-py-deprecated.html.

Rename default branch to main

The development is switching from git-flow to a trunk based model
because the overhead of git-flow was not needed for the size of the
project.
Reduce stray output from test

Remove --strict-search, --uid and --target-uid

These command line options have been deprecated for some time now.
See cd4925c3e4143f08004d789b4ed6b6cd2d15cb79
and ed2d26a394d252853c2fa8db16d26b4cfa075a98.
